This are a handful of scripts to run Igor testsuites on oVirt Node.

= Building the RPM =
Should be:

 $ sudo yum groupinstall fedora-packager
 $ make rpm

The RPM will be placed in the default ~/rpmbuild/RPMS/noarch dir


= Exporting the RPMs =
This is needed to edit-node can pick it up (see next section).
Should be:
 $ cd ~/rpmbuild/RPMS/noarch
 $ createrepo .
 $ <open firewall port 8081>
 $ python -m SimpleHTTPServer 8081


= Editing an existing oVirt Node image with edit-node =
Should be along the lines:

Assumptions:
- Latest upstream ovirt-node release

 $ cat autotesting.repo
 [autotesting]
 name=Autotesting (Igor)
 baseurl=http://127.0.0.1:8081
 enabled=1
 metadata_expire=1m
 gpgcheck=0
 
 $ sudo ./edit-node --verbose --debug --repo=autotesting.repo --install=ovirt-autotesting-systemd ovirt-node-iso-2.6.0-20130212.fc18.iso
